Here's a clear step-by-step guide for installing XCompact3d on TAMU's Faster HPC:

Login and Create Directory

bashCopyssh NetID@faster.hprc.tamu.edu
cd $HOME
mkdir xcompact3d && cd xcompact3d

Load Required Modules

bashCopymodule purge
module load GCCcore/11.3.0
module load CMake/3.29.3
module load gompi/2023a

Clone Repository

bashCopygit clone https://github.com/xcompact3d/Incompact3d
cd Incompact3d

Set Fortran Compiler

bashCopyexport FC=mpif90

Configure and Build

bashCopycmake -S . -B build
cmake --build build -j 8
The executable will be created at build/bin/xcompact3d
